commit.message: CI: add libxdamage
all: Refactor to much nicer fb abstraction that is less absolutely terrifying
drm: Hook up UsesModifiers for backend
wlserver: Only send Gamescope screenshot feedback if it was initiated from wl
steamcompmgr: Wipe global_focus XDGs when we get the xdg shell windows
wlserver: Handle xdg_toplevel destruction stuff
vblankmanager: Fix external display redzone scaling logic
vblankmanager: Move VBLANK_DEBUG to Convar
drm: Use a dummy always signalled point for IN_FENCE_FD
all: Use mHz everywhere for refresh rate stuff

layer: Remove superfluous canBypassXWayland call

This should be isBypassingXWayland on the swapchain
ime: Add support for Steam Input pointer/button things in new version
protocol: Add Steam Input pointer/button things to gamescope_input_method_manager

ime: Allow multiple IMEs at once

We need this for VR and other input stuff to play nicely
drm: Fix 60hz default since refactor
steamcompmgr: Fix shutdown with --mangoapp
steamcompmgr: Reset signal stuff in spawn_client
rendervulkan: Fix garbage texture because oops typo
wayland_backend: VRR support
drm: Nudge steamcompmgr in page_flip_handler
wayland_backend: Nudge steamcompmgr in _Presented
wlserver: Unfortunately make wlr_drm
wlserver, steamcompmgr: Support for explicit sync
wlserver: Update to wlroots 0.18

wlserver: Remove gamescope_tearing_control + impl

Obsoleted by the layer. If we care about upstream protocol someday when it stops sucking we can add this back.

sucking = not enough info for us to actually determine if we want. I just want to know the damn present mode!

layer, wlserver: Implement fifo with gamescope_swapchain for now

Protocol still won't land for a while, let's get this usable everywhere without driver changes.
wayland_backend: Update cursor on Keyboard_Enter
wayland_backend: Use default cursor when not grabbed
vr_session: Fix crash with NULL m_pchOverlayIcon
wayland_backend: Fallback to 8bpc formats if 10bpc is not available
